h3. Summary

The restAPI call to create a repository with privateKey authentication has been documented with a format that is not correct and produces a private key that is store in Fisheye in an incorrect format. This impact authentication of the repositories affected with the server.

Furthermore, the call required a public key, where as the same operation in the Fisheye UI does not. 
h3. Environment

Issue seen/reproduced in the following versions:
 * Crucible v.3.10, 4.5.1, 4.5.2

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Following the documentation in [Fisheye Crucible REST API|https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/4.5.2/wadl/fecru.html#rest-service-fecru:admin:repositories], create a repository with private key authorization:

POST [http://localhost:8060/rest-service-fecru/admin/repositories]
 Body of the request is JSON formatted:
{code:xml}
{
	"type" : "git",
	"name" : "<reponame>",
	"git" : {
		"location" : "<path-to-git-server-and-repo>",
		"auth" : {
			"authType" : "key",
			"privateKey" :  "-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\\nmyprivatekey\\n....\\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\\n",
			"publicKey" : "ssh-rsa mypublickey public-key-name"
		}
	}
}
{code}
h3. Expected Results

Can authorize, and private key is correctly formatted in $FISHEYE_INST/data/auth/<reponame>
h3. Actual Results

Cannot authorize, and private key is incorrectly formatted in $FISHEYE_INST/data/auth/<reponame> 
n rendered as \n, and not parsed as newline
h3. Notes

There is another issue(s) with this restAPI call:
 # It requires a public key, where as the same authorization operation in the Fisheye UI requires only an upload of a private key, as documented in [Authentication - |https://confluence.atlassian.com/fisheye/authentication-298976915.html#Authentication-privatekey]
 If you use API without "publicKey" specified in the body, it throws the error:
{code:xml}
{
    "code": "IllegalArgument",
    "message": "auth.authType == 'key', to set the ssh key provide both public and private keys"
}
{code}
 # A repository created through the restAPI with privateKey authorization, is documented in the UI as having "Generate Key Pair for ssh" Authorization style. This was already filed as bug though in https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/FE-6561

h3. Workaround
Use the following format:
{noformat}
"privateKey" :  "-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\nmyprivatekey\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
{noformat}

h3. Summary
Creating review with REST API will auto populate negative value into the Send Reminder setting

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create review with due date (2 days later at 12am) like the following data for the REST call http://localhost:8060/rest-service/reviews-v1
{noformat}
{
  "reviewData": {
    "allowReviewersToJoin": true, 
    "author": {
      "userName": "admin"
    }, 
    "creator": {
      "userName": "admin"
    }, 
    "dueDate": "2018-03-22T00:00:00.000+0800", 
    "moderator": {
      "userName": "admin"
    }, 
    "name": "crucible-test", 
    "projectKey": "CR", 
    "type": "REVIEW"
  }
}
{noformat}
# Edit the review to check the Send Reminder setting

h3. Expected Results
Send Reminder will have the default value "1" working day before 

h3. Actual Results
Send Reminder showing negative value "-2" working day before
 
h3. Notes
* Due date 1 days later will have Send Reminder  "-3" working day before and it couldn't be edited
* Due date 3 days later will have Send Reminder  "-1" working day before
* Forth day onwards will have Send Reminder  "0" working day before
